Gotthiel is the worst teacher ever.  Wait calling him a teacher is too generous.  For his lecture he picks 1 section of the chapter and takes the entire period to explain; ignores everything else.  The material is easy, but the test was grading was ****.  Oh yea, and I heard used to be an economic advisor for Jimmy Carter.  Great work Gotthiel.

Pop quizzes suck. Lectures are oversimplified compared to exam and homework questions, thereby incredibly dull. Gothiell overall has a terrible course setup and sucks at teaching through lecture. Spends most of his time talking about rich people and how he sells his book to unsuspecting schools.

his text book s sucks. and his TAs+ tests are confusing. his class is good for non-business major students since he doesnt cover any useful material that help you to understand further business concepts. totally a wasted class.
Honestly, the guy isn't so bad.  He get lost very easily, but if you read the material and listen to his stories, it may just help you, as it does for me.

Decent teacher. I think he'd be better with a more interesting topic; the class is so easy and moves so slowly, I don't think you can make it much more interesting without totally re-doing the curriculum. The whole "buy my new edition every year thing" is what gets me... an Econ professor should know the effects of that on student financials.
